  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Increasing vaccination demand in rural settings via Facebook-2</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The aim of this project is to pilot and test a new and innovative approach to encourage vaccination demand. Simultaneously research activities will monitor and evaluate the effectiveness of the approach. The data gathered will be used to understand the influence of social networks on immunization decision-making and access. It will measure whether or not the intervention has improved timely health seeking behaviour towards child vaccination among caregivers in rural Kachin. The project will work in 15 selected villages of the Kachin State, Myanmar. Facebook (Page, Groups, Chatbot) will be used as an innovative communication tool. The partner, Koe Koe Tech will involve in the deveopment of facbook chatbot and contents. It will be implemented with another partner, KMSS and the capacity of KMSS will be strengthened to manage the program effectively and deliver quality health care services. It is also intended to promote CA visibility in engaging with government, faith leaders through joint activities, some support and active participation in coordination and relationship building.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The people in the targted community will get the health information about immunization with the use of social media which will leed to increasing community demand for vaccination and as an impact, reducing vaccination drop out rates and reducing the prevalence of vaccine preventable disease. It will build confidence by fostering community trust around immunization services by leveraging influential individuals in caregiver networks. By creating or strengthening a social bandwagon effect, it will address complacency issues. And providing real time, practical information on schedules, points and times of access will improve convenience, enabling caregivers to coordinate visits, which will reduce waiting times.</narrative>
  </description>
